# XSS (DOM) - Low

## Step 1

* Opened XSS (DOM) page.
* Security level set to Low.

![01_target_page](images/01_target_page.jpg)

## Step 2

* Modified the `default` URL parameter.

**Payload**

```html
<script>alert(1)</script>
```

* JavaScript executed successfully in the browser.

![02_xss_execution](images/02_xss_execution.jpg)

## Result

* DOM Based Cross Site Scripting was successfully exploited.
* Arbitrary JavaScript executed in the victim's browser.

## Reason

* No input validation or filtering is implemented.
* User-controlled data is inserted into the DOM.

## Fix

* Validate and sanitize user input.
* Use safe DOM APIs.
* Encode untrusted data before inserting it into the page.
* Implement Content Security Policy (CSP).
